# strict enforceable rules

- always read the file entirely before editing
- match the existing code style exactly
- strong typing is required
- no `any` types in typescript
- no `console.log()` in production code (use a proper logger or remove before committing)
- prefer `const` over `let` whenever possible
- imports must be sorted logically (built-in, vendor, internal)
- unit tests are strictly required for new logic
- commit message format: `type(scope): description` (e.g., `feat(auth): add login route`)
- absolutely no secrets or credentials hardcoded
